td.h2: ElevenLabs introduces a voice assistant that lets you act on tools like Perplexity and Notion

td.p: 4,284 Likes
11.ai is a voice-first AI assistant that allows you to execute tasks using natural language. It connects to tools like Gmail, Notion, Slack, and Linear along with support for custom MCP integrations.
It supports more than 5,000 prebuilt voices and offers voice cloning to create a personalized assistant.
11.ai supports both voice and text in the same session and detects language automatically

li.p: Plan your day and write tasks to Notion or Linear
Search Slack messages or emails and summarize key updates
Create and manage Linear tickets via voice
Research topics using Perplexity and outline findings
Runs on ElevenLabs' Conversational AI platform
Detects almost 70+ languages automatically for multilingual interaction
Maintains conversational flow across multi-step interactions
Available as a proof of concept in alpha with free access for now
Get started by singing up, selecting a voice, and integrating tools

p.em: "We need an app or an option to add the agent somewhere. Having to go to the site to start a call manually every time creates the friction that will keep me from using it practically. Otherwise, I'm signed up, tried it, love it, and excited to see the next steps"

"So far the voice has highs and lows regarding intonation while formulating a long sentence. Sometimes it screams sometimes it kinda whispers , also it cant laugh or sing or express those subtle nuances of human emotions."
"Tried this too - looks like the issue is that 11ai doesn't support oauth auth for MCP, otherwise these docs would work"

td.p: ☆ 4,539 Stars

Use this OpenAI repo to read files, run terminal commands, and write Python code. The system solves 85% of software engineering problems in SWE-bench Lite. It tracks actions, stores memory, and handles errors during long tasks.
☆ 33,284 Stars
This repo lets you run a local AI assistant on your computer without internet. You can use open-source models like Llama and Qwen, or connect to OpenAI and Anthropic models using the API.
☆ 11,538 Stars
Automate tasks across apps like Slack, Gmail, and Notion without writing code. Run locally with Docker and keep everything synced securely on your own server.

td.h2: Automate Browser Tasks from Video with Gemini

td.p: 738 Likes

This lecture explains how Gemini 2.5 Pro automates browser tasks. It learns from your screen recordings by parsing video frames and audio. It then generates automation scripts that run directly in your browser.
You will learn:

li.p: How to upload and process videos inside the Gemini app
How to run these automations inside Chrome, Edge, or Brave
How to reuse workflows or build new ones from recorded tasks without coding
